blueprint.label: Vanilla Refueling Station
blueprint.description:
OPTIONAL

This accepts (non-standard) trains with the BT:Refuel interrupt and loads all engines with the current fuel (as provided by the "Fuel Train").  It also unloads the arriving engines of any previous fuel type and sends that to a Provider station where it can either remain indefinitely or be requested by a matching Requester station (not included).

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Calculate the average number of items per chest.
Using only the first car because a short-train could leave it empty while later cars make the station think it has capacity.

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description: This station is does not accept "general" trains and thus does not have the logic associated with it.  It's much more simply managed and depends on the "special" dedicated Fuel Train for its deliveries.

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description: This provides to the standard network but doesn't utilize the normal logic.  Instead, as long as the station has had something for 60s or longer, it will allow a train to came and take everything to a dedicated "recycling" requester.
